quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  2,142,"The foolish among the people will say, ‘What has turned them away from the qiblah they were following?’ Say, ‘To Allah belong the east and the west. He guides whomever He wishes to a straight path.’"
  2,143,"Thus We have made you a middle nation that you may be witnesses to the people, and that the Apostle may be a witness to you. We did not appoint the qiblah you were following, but that We may ascertain those who follow the Apostle from those who turn back on their heels. It was indeed a hard thing except for those whom Allah has guided. And Allah would not let your prayers go to waste. Indeed Allah is most kind and merciful to mankind"
  2,144,"We certainly see you turning your face about in the sky. We will surely turn you to a qiblah of your liking: so turn your face towards the Holy Mosque, and wherever you may be, turn your faces towards it! Indeed those who were given the Book surely know that it is the truth from their Lord. And Allah is not oblivious of what they do"
  2,145,"Even if you bring those who were given the Book every [kind of] sign, they will not follow your qiblah. Nor shall you follow their qiblah, nor will any of them follow the qiblah of the other. And if you follow their desires, after the knowledge that has come to you, you will be one of the wrongdoers"
  2,146,"Those whom We have given the Book recognize him just as they recognize their sons, but a part of them indeed conceal the truth while they know"
  2,147,This is the truth from your Lord; so do not be among the skeptics
  2,148,"Everyone has a cynosure to which he turns; so take the lead in all good works. Wherever you may be, Allah will bring you all together. Indeed Allah has power over all things"
  2,149,"Whencesoever you may go out, turn your face towards the Holy Mosque. Indeed it is the truth from your Lord, and Allah is not oblivious of what you do"
  2,150,"And whencesoever you may go out, turn your face towards the Holy Mosque, and wherever you may be, turn your faces towards it, so that the people may have no allegation against you, neither those of them who are wrongdoers. So do not fear them, but fear Me, that I may complete My blessing on you and so that you may be guided"
  2,151,"Even as We sent to you an apostle from among yourselves, who recites to you Our signs and purifies you, and teaches you the Book and wisdom, and teaches you what you did not know"
  2,152,"Remember Me and I will remember you, and thank Me, and do not be ungrateful to Me"
  2,153,O you who have faith! Take recourse in patience and prayer; indeed Allah is with the patient
  2,154,"Do not call those who were slain in Allah’s way ‘dead.’ No, they are living, but you are not aware"
  2,155,"We will surely test you with a measure of fear and hunger and a loss of wealth, lives, and fruits; and give good news to the patient"
  2,156,"—those who, when an affliction visits them, say, ‘Indeed we belong to Allah and to Him do we indeed return.’"
  2,157,"It is they who receive the blessings of their Lord and [His] mercy, and it is they who are the [rightly] guided"